@startuml fig-A03-message-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title PCAP Report Generator — E2 End-to-End Pipeline

participant "Bash\nscripts/" as SH #ECEFF1
participant "h1\n(client)" as H1 #FFE0B2
participant "s1 (switch\nwith delay/loss)" as SW #BBDEFB
participant "h2\n(web server)" as H2 #C8E6C9
participant "h3\n(DNS)" as H3 #E1BEE7
participant "tcpdump" as CAP #ECEFF1
participant "Report\nTool" as TOOL #E1BEE7

== TRAFFIC GENERATION ==

SH -> SW : tc qdisc: add 50 ms delay + 2% loss
H1 -> SW : DNS query (h2.lab)
SW -> H3 : forward
H3 --> SW : DNS response
SW --> H1 : DNS response
note right of CAP : R3: ip >= 50

H1 -> SW : TCP SYN → h2:80
SW -> H2 : SYN (delayed)
H2 --> SW : SYN-ACK
SW --> H1 : SYN-ACK
H1 -> SW : ACK + HTTP GET
H2 --> H1 : HTTP 200 + payload

H1 -[#FF9800]> SW : large TCP transfer
SW -[#FF9800]> H2 : segments (some lost)
H2 -[#E53935]-> SW : retransmission
note right of CAP : R1: tcp >= 50\nR2: tcp.analysis.retransmission >= 1

== CAPTURE AND ANALYSIS ==

SW -> CAP : stop capture → traffic_e2.pcap
SH -> TOOL : analyse traffic_e2.pcap
TOOL -> TOOL : parse → aggregate flows\n→ compute RTT, retransmissions\n→ rank top talkers

TOOL -> SH : report.md + metrics.json
note right of TOOL : verify with tshark\nStatistics → Conversations

legend right
  The report includes: top talkers (bytes),
  flow count, TCP retransmissions per flow
  and estimated RTT (median). Each metric
  is linked to a tshark filter for validation.
endlegend
@enduml
